This paper deals with estimating the number of distinct n-grams in text or bioinformatics databases, which is a problem related to data management and information retrieval (cs.DB, cs.IR). The paper also discusses the use of hashing algorithms, which are commonly used in data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper presents a novel algorithm for estimating n-gram statistics, which involves statistical analysis and machine learning techniques (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the security implications of hashing algorithms, which is a topic related to cryptography (cs.CR).
